p2
VViolin meets sitar
p3
sVnews
p4
VCommemorating the beginning of the fourth decade of fruitful existence serving the cause of Indian classical music, Visakha Music Academy organised a grand function at Kalabharati with Sadguru K. Sivananda Murty as the chief guest. Noted exponent of \u000acarnatic music on violin, G.J.R. Krishnan (son and disciple of violin maestro Lalgudi G. Jayaraman) in the learned company of one of the prime disciples of Pt. Ravisankar, Gaurab Mazumdar on sitar, rendered a soothing recital. Bangalore-based Praveen on mridangam and Ashok Chakraborthy lent excellent support to the violinist and sitarist respectively. They also rendered an eruditelayavinyasamwith verve after ragam tanam pallavi in Keeravani.Krishnan and Gaurab earlier got off to a scintillating start playingManasukarugaof Patnam Subrahmanya Iyer (Hamsadhvani) adorned with ragam and swaram in the two tempos. Playing of the MeerabhajanVaishnavajanathu(Misra Kamaj) and a dhun in Sindhubhairavi, marked the concluding piece.
